Class NCIntentSolver.INTENT

    public static class NCIntentSolver.INTENT
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Token solver intent.

    Intent is similar in idea to a regular expressions. Just like regular expression defines a search pattern for text, the intent defines a search pattern for the list of tokens. Intent has hierarchical structure: it consists of TERMs, where each term consists of ITEMs where each item is a predicate (RULE or one of the logical combinators) with quantifiers.
    See Also:
    CONV_INTENT, NON_CONV_INTENT, Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • INTENT

        public INTENT(String id,
              boolean inclConv,
              boolean ordered,
              NCIntentSolver.TERM... terms)
        Creates new intent with given parameters.
        Parameters:
        id - Intent ID. It can be any arbitrary string meaningful for the developer. Look at the example for one approach to provide descriptive intent IDs.
        inclConv - Whether or not to include conversation into the search for this intent. If conversation is not included than only the tokens present in the user input will be considered.
        ordered - Whether or not the specified order of TERMs is important for matching this intent. If intent is unordered its TERMs can be found anywhere in the string and in any order.
        terms - List of TERMs defining this intent.
